==English==

===Etymology===
The word “spa” is rooted in the Latin word sanus per aqua meaning “health through water” and dates back to the Roman times. The city of “Spa” in Belgium, celebrated for its curative waters, got its name from this ancient acronym. Roman “sanus per aqua” inscriptions are found in the city of Spa. Similar Roman baths are found in Baden-Baden (literally Bathing-Bathing) in Germany and in Bath in the United Kingdom.

===Noun===
'''spa'''

# A health resort near a mineral spring or hot spring.
# A trendy or fashionable resort.
# A health club.

